template<typename T >
int CommonNS::split ( std::string  buffer,
const std::string &  delimiter,
std::vector< T > &  result 
)

This function splits the contents of buffer using delimiter as a separator string. The resulting strings are stored in the result vector.

Parameters:
[in]bufferThe input string that will be parsed.
[in]delimiterThe separator. This can be a string of several characters.
[out]resultA vector of type T that will contain the elements from the split operation.
Returns:
Returns the number of elements in result after the split operation.
